page.title: 07HOUSING IN MELBOURNE
page.content: HOUSING IN MELBOURNE IS A COMPLETE MIXTURE OF ALL STYLES,RANGING FROM A CRUCK COTTAGE IN THE HIGH STREET WHICH HAS ORIGINAL 14TH CENTURY CRUCKS STILL INTACT,TO IMPRESSIVE GEORGIAN AND VICTORIAN HOUSES AND 20TH CENTURY COUNCIL AND PRIVATE ESTATE SEMI_DETACHED HOUSES.ALTHOUGH MELBOURNE HAS CAREFULLY PRESERVED MANY OF ITS HISTORIC HOUSES,IT HAS ALSO ENCOURAGED MODERN HOUSING TO FIT IN CAREFULLY WITH THEM.TWO LARGE,MODERN, PRIVATE ESTATES OF RED BRICK HOUSES HAVE BEEN BUILT ON THE OUTSKIRTS OF THE TOWN WHICH DO NOT INTERFERE WITH THE MORE TRADITIONAL HOUSING.THE COUNTY COUNCIL BUILT MANY COUNCIL HOUSES SINCE THE END OF THE 1ST WORLD WAR BUT MANY OF THESE HAVE BEEN BOUGHT BY THEIR OCCUPANTS IN THE 1980'S.OLDER SLUM TYPE HOUSES IN THE NEW YORK DISTRICT WERE CLEARED IN THE 1950'S.
